Configure team sync

Wire engram memory sharing via git hooks.
post-merge: import team memories after pull/merge.
pre-push:   export your memories and remind to commit .engram/.

! Scope-leak warning: engram sync has no scope filter.
  scope:personal memories for this project WILL be committed to git.
  Mitigations:
    (a) Wrap sensitive content in <private>…</private> tags.
    (b) Use a separate project name for personal memories.

! Hook framework conflict: husky is configured (.husky/ directory found)
  Hooks cannot be written automatically. Run these in your framework:
    post-merge: engram sync --import || true
    pre-push:   engram sync --project 'my-team' || true               
